article.description: — Marcellus Earlington tied his season high with 23 points as San Diego beat Pacific 73-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Earlington scores 23 to lead San Diego past Pacific 73-65
article.linkText: Earlington scores 23 to lead San Diego past Pacific 73-65
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- — Marcellus Earlington tied his season high with 23 points as San Diego beat Pacific 73-65 on Saturday. Wayne McKinney II had 16 points and six assists for San Diego (11-8, 4-2 West Coast Conference). Pierre Crockrell II scored a career-high 24 points for the Tigers (5-12, 0-3), who have now lost six straight games. Luke Avdalovic added 15 points. Nick Blake had 13 points. Alphonso Anderson had six points and 11 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
